5. Basic Configuration
1. Power on the device – a Wi-Fi network will be created:
 SSID: BasicLine_S3
 Password: 12345678
2. Open a web browser and navigate to:
 http://192.168.4.1
3. In the Settings section, adjust the following parameters:
 – T_ON – temperature to start cooling
 – T_OFF – temperature to stop cooling
 – T_SPRAY – spray activation temperature
 – HYST – stage hysteresis step
 – Power Monitor – enable or disable power measurement
4. Click Save – values are validated and written to EEPROM.



6. System Functions
Function
Description
Automatic fan cascade
Activates fans stepwise according to Tout temperature.
Fan rotation
Changes active branches every hour (1–3).
Reverse cycle
Runs a 5 s reverse after compressor start.
Spray control
Activates relay R5 above T_SPRAY.
Thermal Health Score
Calculates system performance (0–100 %).
Service Timer
Displays SERVICE DUE after 1000 operating hours.
Power Monitor
Measures fan power input.
Watchdog
Resets system after 10 s of no response.
Dirty EEPROM commit
Writes changes only when updated, extends EEPROM life.

